the reason i mentioned the example with the focus2 item was that the mob is of the same difficulty as some mobs that drop focus3.<br>
And also because lots of items that are popular and regarded as high quality among lv51-59 players are dropped by mobs like that.<br>
A few of them got focus3 but focus2 is more common.<br>
And it was also to explain why I think the risk/reward ratio is strange in some cases.<br>
<br>
If one player bought a good item for perhaps 5Kpp before the patch and his friend also bought a new item for 5K of the same quality.<br>
And also if the mobs that drop them are the same difficulty.<br>
Then you can understand that the player thinks it´s strange that his item was given a focus2 effect if the other item got focus3.<br>
The fact that a lv44 group cant kill the mob and only a few lv44 can afford the item will make him think that its very strange that it didn´t get focus3. <br>
<br>
If they intended to balance lv51-lv59 players they would have put focus3 effects on items that are common among those players. At least among well equipped lv51-59 players.<br>
They did not.<br>
<br>
Only a few lv60 players are members of high end guilds.<br>
Most of them are members of medium strong guilds.<br>
The focus3 items are not very difficult to get for those lv60 players.<br>
At least not as difficult as they are for lv51-59 players.<br>
Because they are killing the raid mobs that drop focus3 every week.<br>
Those are the mobs that a guild like that would normaly kill to make progress.<br>
You can get 1 out 4 focus3 items, you think. The lv60 player in such guild can get 4 out of 4.<br>
So it´s much easier at lv60 compared to lv51-59.<br>
High-end players are an exception. Perhaps the fact that they no longer kill the raid mobs that drop them means that they have the same chanse as lv51-lv59 players to get a focus3 item.<br>
But thats not relevant if we want to compare lv51-59 players with lv60 players in general.<br>
<br>
I think I have proved my point that it´s more difficult for a lv51-59 player to get a focus3 item compared to most(not all) lv60 players.<br>
